THE GREATEST MARATHA WARRIOR KING AND THE BEST INDIAN RULER OF HIS TIMES.

CHATRAPATI SHIVAJI

Produced, Directed, Story, Screenplay, and Dialogues by Bhalji Pendharkar , 
Music by C. Ramchandra , 
Lyric by P. Sawalaram, Bhalji Pendharkar and Shailendra, 
Playback Singer : Lata Mangeshkar, 
Lighting by G. Shinde, 
Sound Recording: Jadhav and Mole, 
Art Direction by Ganpatrao wadangekar,
Still Photography by Dada Gajbar, 
Make-up by Marathe and Jadhav, 
Dress designed by Vishwasrao, 
Dance directed by Hazarilal, Aadamsaheb, Kumar Atre and Kusum, 
Location: Jayprabha Studios (Kolhapur).

Songs: 
Kuni Govind ghya kuni Gopal ghya, 
Wajav danka dahi dishela, 
Yare ya veer ya shur ya, 
Gawat gaon mazh maherch gaon, 
Muzhpe hi raham mere, 
Chhan chhabeli mi albeli, 
Sata janmichi son paule, 
Dhwaj tejalun swatantryacha, 
Shivarayache roop pahawe.

The first hindi song written by Shilenra for Marathi movie, 
Lata Mangeshkar's last movie as an actress. 
The same movie was also dubbed in Hindi. 
Parshwnath Aaltekar played Mirza raje Jaysingh in Marathi version whereas Pruthvi Raj Kapoor played the same role in Hindi version.

